    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>creamy stock</strong> to the pan with 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat – this is your <strong>creamy tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Once boiling, remove the pan from the heat and stir through your <strong>gnocchi </strong>(this will cook in the oven later!)</p><p>Transfer the contents of the pan<strong> </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and top with the <strong>torn mozzarella</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
